<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1939-09-07T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1939-09-07T00:00:00-05:00" n="952" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d952">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">811.24 Raw Materials/3002: Telegram</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the Ambassador in the United Kingdom</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Kennedy</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1939-09-07">September 7,
                                1939</date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>827. Your 1486, September 6, 8 p.m., paragraph 2. The American Minister
                            at The Hague has been requested to press the Netherland Government for
                            agreement to the proposed special 10 percent release for the fourth
                            quarter and to keep you informed directly. Please keep The Hague
                            informed regarding developments in London affecting rubber.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>